properties.areaDesc: Orange County Coastal; San Diego County Coastal Areas
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 1 at 4:57AM PST until January 4 at 4:00AM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
...A LONG PERIOD WEST-NORTHWEST SWELL FROM 290 DEGREES WILL
GENERATE HIGH SURF WEDNESDAY EVENING THROUGH EARLY SATURDAY...

.Highest surf will be on the San Diego County beaches south of
Encinitas.

* Surf...For San Diego County, the surf will be 7-10 ft with the
highest sets south of Encinitas. For Orange County, the surf
will be 5-7 ft.

* Timing...Surf will build tonight into Thursday, peaking
Thursday afternoon, then subside Friday night but is expected to
remain elevated through the weekend.

* Tides...High tide 3.9 ft at 3 PM Thursday and 4.1 ft at 4 PM
Friday.

* Impacts...Dangerous swimming conditions and a high risk of rip
currents. Local beach erosion possible.
properties.instruction:
A High Surf Advisory means that high surf will affect beaches in
the advisory area...producing localized beach erosion and
dangerous swimming conditions.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 4 AM PST SATURDAY
